  "accepted_findings": [
    "The family-count threshold is met with five independently authored adult forms and three independently authored intermediate forms; no form is a transformed copy.",
    "Competition lean, azimuth-sector suppression, vertical crown gaps, deterministic storm breakage, and release growth now alter source geometry and produce distinct silhouettes in both turntable views.",
    "The storm-damaged form reduces near foliage anchors from its undamaged 225-anchor budget to 177 and records six deterministically damaged branches rather than hiding damage in a transform or material.",
    "Explicit native-texture compilation, resident leaf mips, Sharpen5 generation, and 0.50 masked-alpha coverage remove the white fallback quads found by the first v8 run.",
    "Five-kilometre review spacing removes neighboring forms from the meaningful field of the 60 m and 150 m evidence views.",
    "The final UE 5.8 Metal run completes forty captures with zero map-check errors, zero map-check warnings, no material compile errors, and no texture no-miplevel warnings."
  ],
  "rejection_reasons": [
    "Foreground closeups still read as procedural: leaf density is sparse, several branchlets intersect, and twig phyllotaxis lacks the irregular density of a mature native coigue crown.",
    "All eight forms still inherit the same primary branch construction grammar, so repeated horizontal cadence remains visible even though competition, gap, damage, and age controls now vary it.",
    "Shadow-side bark remains too dark for a final foreground asset and has not been calibrated against a measured color target under the fixed review light rig.",
    "Temporal wind coherence, branch-versus-leaf phase lag, measured desktop and VR performance, mixed-species ecology, and source-matched corridor comparison remain untested.",
    "The broader Futaleufu authoring contract still requires sapling/deadwood strata and the other named native species before this coigue family can establish production forest ecology."
  ],
